 wonderful I just bought the latest book on my vacation. Heres the descriptions of the books: <br>
<br>
1~Join a close-knit group of seven best friends and share their lives, their adventures---and their faith. In the first book in the series, Marilyn Thatcher's happy life as a minister's wife is shattered when her husband divorces her for another woman. She is determined to build a new life alone until she meets her new neighbor---and pastor---Joshua Langham. Will she risk her heart again? <br>
<br>
2~Supermodel Kim Lan Lowery has it all--exquisite beauty, wealth, an engagement to famous heartthrob Ted Curry, and a close circle of friends. When a "secret admirer" sends flowers and love notes, Kim is flattered. As the letters become strangely possessive, she desperately searches for someone she can trust. While she grapples with the impact of her faith on her career, Kim senses the Lord tugging her to take part in a mission trip to Vietnam. But when the trip coordinator Mick O'Donnel refuses her application because of her celebrity status, sparks fly. Their lifestyles clash and their values collide, but they also battle a deep undercurrent of passion. Finally embarking on the trip, Kim feels secure--until her "admirer" reveals his true identity.<br>
<br>
3~Join a close-knit group of friends as they share their lives, adventures, and faith. In A SHELTER IN THE STORM, Sonsee LeBlanc must choose between the "facts" and her heart when Taylor Delaney, her long-time friend, is implicated in her father's death. Will their search for the killer lead to paths of forgiveness . . . and love?<br>
<br>
4~When Kinkaide returns six years after his no-show at their wedding, Melissa's heart is still torn by his rejection and the love she secretly harbors. To re-ignite their love, Kinkaide sends Mel an invitation to join him on a Mediterranean cruise (seperate cabins of course!). Melissa's mother secretly sends him an acceptance note "signed" by her daughter. Discovering her mother's duplicity, Melissa is furious and refuses to go to Greece and Italy. At the last minute, she changes her mind and meets a delighted Kinkaide at the airport. As they struggle with old wounds, they meet Desmond and Abby Casper, an African-American couple who hope the cruise will save their marriage. As she works through issues of dominance and disparaging communication, Melissa begins to see how her need to be in control usurps God's authority and creates a barrier to love. With a contrite heart, Melissa turns to God and discovers His forgiveness...and the ability to open her heart once more.<br>
<br>
5~Desperately seeking clues, Jac and Lawton search for the truth behind a brutal crime and overcome the mountains in their own lives to find restoration and a tender, growing love. When Detective Jacquelyn Lightfoot agrees to help Lawton track down the men who beat him and left him for dead, she secretly hopes she'll be able to dampen the computer genius' obvious affection for her. But their mutual attraction grows as the two search for the Mafia boss behind the murderous plot threatening Lawton and for the rare ancient coins that precipitated the violence. When Jac confides that she was once abused and fears the intimacy of a committed relationship, Lawton's tender understanding reveals the depth of his love. A new path opens for Jac, and the Lord's healing work can begin. This book shines with the joy that come from accepting--and extending--God's grace.<br>
<br>
6~Sammie and her young son are starting a new life after the death of her abusive husband. When her high school sweetheart takes over operations at Romantic Living magazine, Sammie vows that This Time Around their relationship will be strictly professional. Will she risk her heart again and accept R.J.'s love?<br>
<br>
